node.text:
Power Bank Explodes on China Southern Flight

The incident happend today during the boarding of China Southern Airlines flight CZ3539 at Guangzhou Baiyun International Airport, China.

The power bank was not being used inside a passenger's carry on luggage when it exploded into flames. A flight attendant and passenger use water and juice to fight the fire.

A new aircraft was dispatched for the flight which departed 3 hours late —
